rename_snapshot(25.10)                                  rename_snapshot(25.10)

Name rename_snapshot - Allows you to rename existing snapshots
Syntax
Parameters  -branch  <newBranch>  Specifies  the  new branch for the snapshot.
       Data_type: string, optional -help Outputs a brief description that  in-
       cludes type and default information for each rename_snapshot parameter.
       For  a  detailed  description of the command and all of its parameters,
       use the man command: man rename_snapshot -id <metricID>  Specifies  the
       metric  database  ID  to change. If you do not specify any id, the tool
       will take current database  as  default.  Data_type:  string,  optional
       Note:  You  can find the uuid of a snapshot by using get_metric for the
       uuid metric. -name <newName> Specifies the new name for  the  snapshot.
       The tool will error out if you set the name to empty string. Data_type:
       string,  optional -uuid <snapshotuuid> Specifies the snapshot UUID. The
       tool will error out if there is no snapshot  with  the  provided  uuid.
       Data_type: string, required
